<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,564,1532,1558]" box="[189,564,1532,1558]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,564,1532,1558]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,564,1532,1558]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Distribution and conservation</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1398,1579,1676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Endemic to south-eastern 
<collectingCountry box="[495,644,1579,1605]" name="South Africa" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">South Africa</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[661,733,1579,1605]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="6.[189,232,1966,1992]" captionTargetBox="[302,1285,1252,1926]" captionTargetId="figure@6.[302,1286,1252,1926]" captionTargetPageId="6" captionText="Fig. 2. Distribution of Afrodonta bilamellaris Melvill &amp; Ponsonby, 1908 (blue circles) and Af. connollyi Solem, 1970 (orange squares). Contour at 1000 m." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3762284" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3762284/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), ranging from northern 
<collectingRegion box="[1023,1207,1579,1605]" country="South Africa" name="KwaZulu-Natal" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">KwaZulu-Natal</collectingRegion>
(Mkhuze Game Reserve) south to eastern E. 
<collectingRegion box="[520,580,1615,1641]" country="South Africa" name="Western Cape" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Cape</collectingRegion>
(Kei Mouth), from the coastal hinterland to the Drakensberg foothills; in leaf-litter of various forest 
<typeStatus box="[535,597,1650,1676]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">types</typeStatus>
and valley thickets. Not of conservation concern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,303,1716,1742]" box="[189,303,1716,1742]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<heading bold="true" box="[189,303,1716,1742]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" reason="3">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,303,1716,1742]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="7.[189,1399,1762,1860]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Originally confused with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Herbert" authorityYear="2020" baseAuthorityName="Connolly" baseAuthorityYear="1933" box="[496,756,1763,1789]" class="Gastropoda" family="Charopidae" genus="Costulodonta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="burnupi" status="gen. et comb. nov">
<emphasis box="[496,756,1763,1789]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Costulodonta burnupi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[765,981,1762,1789]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" rank="species">gen. et comb. nov</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but in that species the protoconch is axially costate, the umbilicus wider, and the upper parietal lamella is weaker, not extending to the aperture edge.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
